ObjectStates.Name: Notecard
ObjectStates.Description:
Since the invaders first started appearing, you’ve found yourself
in more than one terrifying situation as the marines have worked
to drive them back, but this one sets the bar to a new high.

ObjectStates.Name: Notecard
ObjectStates.Description:
You were patrolling the surface of Mars in a UAC rover when
there was an explosion caused by an unknown source, and the
rover was critically damaged

ObjectStates.Name: Notecard
ObjectStates.Description:
The radio and oxygen cylinders in
the rover were totally destroyed. Low on air, you were forced to
make your way to the nearest shelter with atmosphere—a maintenance
base that has yet to be reclaimed from the demons.

ObjectStates.Name: Notecard
ObjectStates.Description:
You begin in the corridor  next to the compromised air lock. Oxygen
hisses out into the chill martian night.

ObjectStates.Name: Notecard
ObjectStates.Description:
Worse, when you were entering, the airlock doors refused to seal
all the way. You were forced to use the grenades you had with
you to blow the inner doors, destroying the atmospheric seal on
the base and letting the oxygen inside start to escape.

ObjectStates.Name: Notecard
ObjectStates.Description:
All you’ve got to defend yourself with is a pistol, and you’re
running out of ammo and air, but even a slim chance at survival
is better than none.

ObjectStates.Name: Notecard
ObjectStates.Description: The Marines must Gather four [0BFF00]"Oxygen Tanks" [000000] so they we have enough air to reach the Garage where they can find another rover

ObjectStates.Name: Custom_Model_Bag
ObjectStates.Description:
[0077FF]These giant invaders are the strongest of the observed
entities. They can knock entire squads aside with one
sweep of their arms. Keep your distance at all costs!

ObjectStates.Name: Custom_Model_Bag
ObjectStates.Description:
[0077FF]These creatures levitate slowly from place to place, spitting
large fireballs that explode in a wide radius.
Cacodemons are extremely difficult to kill, and marines
should use caution when confronting them.

ObjectStates.Name: Custom_Model_Bag
ObjectStates.Description:
[0077FF]These bloated creatures are slow, but they have powerful
guns fused to their arms, allowing them to fire a heavy
barrage of bullets.

ObjectStates.Name: Custom_Model_Bag
ObjectStates.Description:
[0077FF]These humanoid invaders are similar to imps, but employ
a much more powerful pyrokinetic ability that can summon
huge gouts of flame at great distance. Close with
them and engage!

ObjectStates.Name: Custom_Model_Bag
ObjectStates.Description:
[0077FF]Although they are easier to kill than Pinkies, marines
should avoid letting these invaders get within melee
range. Their two heads can attack independently of each
other, and each can inflict severe injury. Like pinkies,
maggots are capable of pre-emptively attacking enemies
who get too close.

end

function bzzt(o, color)
    if lockout == false then
        lockout = true
        self.AssetBundle.playTriggerEffect(0)
        if printFastest == true then
            printToAll(Player[color].steam_name.." pressed the button.", stringColorToRGB(color))
        end
        lockoutTimer()
    end
end

function unlock()
    lockout = false
end

function lockoutTimer()
    Timer.destroy(self.getGUID())
    Timer.create({identifier=self.getGUID(), function_name='unlock', delay=resetDelay})
end
